The article highlights the issue of food loss and waste in the United States. It states that more than one-third of food in the country is lost or wasted, which not only undermines environmental stewardship but also hinders the ability of Americans to lead healthier lives. The article mentions the efforts made by the government to reduce food loss and waste through the Winning on Reducing Food Waste Initiative, a collaborative effort by the Department of Agriculture, Environmental Protection Agency, and Food and Drug Administration. The initiative aims to educate consumers, engage stakeholders, and develop solutions to address the issue. The article also emphasizes the importance of public-private partnerships, such as the United States Food Loss and Waste 2030 Champions, in improving the efficiency and management of food systems. It encourages all Americans to contribute to reducing food loss and waste during Winning on Reducing Food Waste Month.